The paper deals with algorithmic problems related to graph theory and optimization, which are typically studied in computer science sub-categories such as cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), cs.CG (Computational Geometry), cs.CC (Computational Complexity), and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The first part of the paper focuses on designing approximation algorithms for the Hub Labeling problem, which is a preprocessing technique for shortest path queries. This falls under the scope of cs.DS and cs.CG. The second part of the paper deals with the stability model for graph partitioning and clustering problems, which is a topic of interest in cs.DM, cs.CC, and cs.LG. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper are cs.DS, cs.DM, cs.CG, cs.CC, and cs.LG, in that order.
